This looks satisfying but in reality you’re not supposed to remove them. They’re called sebaceous filaments. it’s normal to have them on skin so you can’t get rid of them. removing them is only temporary—they always come back. Avoid squeezing sebaceous filaments in an attempt to remove them. If you try to get rid of sebaceous filaments by squeezing may injure the skin and damage your pore, even making it bigger in the process.
